'''Álvaro David Montero Perales''' (born 29 March 1995) is a Colombian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Argentine Primera División]] club [[Club Atlético Vélez Sarsfield|Vélez Sarsfield]], on loan from [[Categoría Primera A]] club [[Millonarios F.C.|Millonarios]] and the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]].<ref>[http://colombia.as.com/colombia/2015/07/09/futbol/1436408851_151647.html Álvaro Montero firma por cuatro años con San Lorenzo]</ref>

==International==
Montero made his [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]] debut on 3 June 2019, in a friendly against Panama, as a 77th-minute substitute for [[David Ospina]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=539194|title=Colombia v Panama game report|date=3 June 2019}}</ref>

